<div class="ArticleView">
        <img src="/upload/UD/Ingressbilder/TemaIngress/MR_dialog_En_100x75.jpg" alt="" class="ArticleImg" />
        
        
        <div class="ArticleImgContent">
            <h2><a href="/en/dep/ud/selected-topics/human-rights/norways-human-rights-dialogues/dialogues.html?id=447059">Norway’s human rights dialogues</a></h2>        
                
            <p>
               Norway has started to cooperate more closely with countries where there are human rights challenges, but where there is also potential for improvement through dialogue and contact. Currently, Norway is engaged in formal human rights dialogues of this kind with China, Indonesia and Vietnam. 
            </p>
            
        </div>
    </div>
    
    


<div class="ArticleView">
        <img src="/upload/UD/Ingressbilder/TemaIngress/MR_urfolk_EN_100x75.jpg" alt="" class="ArticleImg" />
        
        
        <div class="ArticleImgContent">
            <h2><a href="/en/dep/ud/selected-topics/human-rights/menneskerettigheter-urfolk/indigenous-peoples-in-development-cooper.html?id=447051">Indigenous peoples in development cooperation</a></h2>        
                
            <p>
               One of the aims of Norwegian development cooperation is to increase the focus on indigenous peoples, while taking an integrated approach to cooperation on indigenous issues.
            </p>
            
        </div>
    </div>
    
    

