                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/aktuelt/taler_artikler/utenriksministeren/2010/mr_beskyttelse.html?id=613531" title="">
                        Strengthening Protection for Human Rights Defenders
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none">Litteraturhuset, Oslo, 3 September 2010</h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Speech/article, Ministry of Foreign Affairs, 03.09.2010]</p>
                <p>We are now issuing guidelines on human rights defenders for our embassies – to enhance our efforts at the bilateral level. The guidelines set out a variety of actions that will enable our embassies to support and protect human rights defenders, Foreign Minister Støre said in his opening address at the seminar in Oslo 3 September 2010.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                <span id="ctl00_FullRegion_CenterAndRightRegion_CenterRegion_SubjectManager_wp290069162_wp708866878_lstSearchResult_lstUniversal_ctl02_Label1"></span>                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/mostafaei_sikkerhet.html?id=612010" title="">
                        Foreign Minister Støre pleased that Mostafaei is safe
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Press release, Ministry of Foreign Affairs, 08.08.2010]</p>
                <p>“I am very pleased that human rights lawyer Mohammad Mostafaei is now safe in Norway,” said Foreign Minister Jonas Gahr Støre.    </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                <span id="ctl00_FullRegion_CenterAndRightRegion_CenterRegion_SubjectManager_wp290069162_wp708866878_lstSearchResult_lstUniversal_ctl03_Label1"></span>                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/cuba-2.html?id=611241" title="">
                        Norway welcomes the release of political prisoners in Cuba 
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Press release, Ministry of Foreign Affairs, 08.07.2010]</p>
                <p>Norwegian Foreign Minister Jonas Gahr Støre commented: “Norway, together with the EU, has steadfastly demanded the unconditional release of political prisoners in Cuba. We were very pleased to receive the news today that the Cuban authorities will release 52 political prisoners.”</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                <span id="ctl00_FullRegion_CenterAndRightRegion_CenterRegion_SubjectManager_wp290069162_wp708866878_lstSearchResult_lstUniversal_ctl04_Label1"></span>                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/aktuelt/nyheter/2010/syria_mr.html?id=611220" title="">
                        Norway deplores sentences against Syrian human rights defenders
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[News story, Ministry of Foreign Affairs, 08.07.2010]</p>
                <p>“The Norwegian Government deplores these sentences and calls on Syria to abide by its international commitments, and in particular by the International Covenant on Civil and Political Rights, which guarantees freedom of opinion and expression,” said State Secretary Espen Barth Eide. </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                <span id="ctl00_FullRegion_CenterAndRightRegion_CenterRegion_SubjectManager_wp290069162_wp708866878_lstSearchResult_lstUniversal_ctl05_Label1"></span>                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            <a href="/en/dep/ud/aktuelt/nyheter/2010/iran.html?id=611057" class="ISI_IGNORE">
                <img src="/upload/UD/Ingressbilder/iran_flag.gif" alt="" class="ArticleImg" />
            </a>
            <div class="ArticleImgContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/aktuelt/nyheter/2010/iran.html?id=611057" title="">
                        Norway condemns death sentences in Iran
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[News story, Ministry of Foreign Affairs, 05.07.2010]</p>
                <p>6 July, State Secretary Espen Barth Eide summoned the Iranian Ambassador, Seyed Hossein Rezvani, to the Ministry of Foreign Affairs in connection with two death sentences in Iran.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                <span id="ctl00_FullRegion_CenterAndRightRegion_CenterRegion_SubjectManager_wp290069162_wp708866878_lstSearchResult_lstUniversal_ctl06_Label1"></span>                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/iran_kritikk.html?id=608466" title="">
                        Norway endorses strong criticism of Iran in the Human Rights Council
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Press release, Ministry of Foreign Affairs, 15.06.2010]</p>
                <p>In the UN Human Rights Council today, Norway criticised the human rights situation in Iran on behalf of more than 50 countries. The joint statement was timed to coincide with the one-year anniversary of the controversial presidential election in Iran.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                <span id="ctl00_FullRegion_CenterAndRightRegion_CenterRegion_SubjectManager_wp290069162_wp708866878_lstSearchResult_lstUniversal_ctl07_Label1"></span>                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/aktuelt/nyheter/2010/drap_bahizire.html?id=607407" title="">
                        Norway concerned about killing of Congolese human rights defender
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[News story, Ministry of Foreign Affairs, 04.06.2010]</p>
                <p>“We were very concerned to learn that the Congolese human rights defender Floribert Chebeya Bahizire has been killed,” said State Secretary Gry Larsen at the Ministry of Foreign Affairs.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                <span id="ctl00_FullRegion_CenterAndRightRegion_CenterRegion_SubjectManager_wp290069162_wp708866878_lstSearchResult_lstUniversal_ctl08_Label1"></span>                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/aktuelt/taler_artikler/utenriksministeren/2010/rights_change.html?id=606791" title="">
                        Human Rights - Empowerment for Change
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none">Oslo, Litteraturhuset, 30 May 2010</h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Speech/article, Ministry of Foreign Affairs, 30.05.2010]</p>
                <p>I believe we need to remain focused on the critically important point of departure: that we are dealing with humankind, that humankind is global, that universal human rights are global, and that we need to approach them as such, as we deal with their empowering potential, Mr Støre said in his intervention.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                <span id="ctl00_FullRegion_CenterAndRightRegion_CenterRegion_SubjectManager_wp290069162_wp708866878_lstSearchResult_lstUniversal_ctl09_Label1"></span>                 
           </div>
